OL,3,CVolunteers helping thousands of toads
OL,4,Ccross the road safely
OL,6,FCollectively they will spend more than
OL,7,F600 hours in hi-vis jackets, armed
OL,8,Fwith torches and buckets walking
OL,9,Fslowly up and down the road.
OL,11,FToads, frogs and newts are carefully
OL,12,Fpicked up with latex-free, powder-free
OL,13,Fgloves, to avoid any chemicals from
OL,14,Fvolunteer hands affecting them, and
OL,15,Ftaken safely in buckets to drop off
OL,16,Fpoints.
OL,18,FIn 2024, more than 50 volunteers
OL,19,Fhelped 3,225 amphibians across a half-
OL,20,Fmile stretch of Charlcombe Lane.
